---
source: tests/metrics_regression.rs
expression: task_stats
---
Task Stats (Execution Quality)
S2 = average user prompts across sessions linked to task (lower is better)
S4 = debug-loop session rate (5+ repeated error turns, lower is better)
S6 = sessions with mid-session error paste (lower is better)
S9 = sessions with task commit in [session start, session end + 4h] (higher is better)

Task                          Branch                      Commits   Sessions      S2(avg)   S4(loop)  S6(mid-err)     S9(4h)   vs Staging  Grade   
────────────────────────────  ──────────────────────────  ───────  ─────────  ───────────  ─────────  ───────────  ─────────  ───────────  ────────
PAC-999                       codex/PAC-999-task-stat...        1    1/1            15.00       0.0%       100.0%     100.0%        +2/-0  Warning 

`vs Staging` shows +added/-removed lines from `git diff staging...<branch>` for non-integration branches.
Task rows exclude integration/fallback branches and non-ticket task keys.
S9 uses task-linked sessions with known timestamps.
Grade thresholds: Healthy (S2<=4 and S4<20%), Watch (S2<=8 and S4<40%), else Warning.
